  {
    q: "Where should an African Grey's cage be placed?",
    a: "Against a wall, at eye level, in a room the family actually uses — Greys are intensely social and need to watch daily life. Keep the cage well away from the kitchen (PTFE/Teflon fumes are lethal), away from drafts and vents, and out of more than a few hours of direct sun.",
